<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1749,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Body pale brown, with small dark spot near ocellus and some pale brown irroration on crown and pronotum. Face without markings. Antennal pedicel dark brown. Scutellum with longitudinal slight brown bands. Forewing smoky hyaline.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1749,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">
Male abdomen: 
<number box="[388,402,1896,1920]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" value="1.0">1</number>
st and 
<number box="[474,488,1896,1920]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" value="2.0">2</number>
nd abdominal tergites illustrated in dorsal view (Fig. K) and 
<number box="[1191,1205,1896,1920]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" value="1.0">1</number>
st and 
<number box="[1277,1291,1896,1920]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" value="2.0">2</number>
nd abdominal sternites illustrated in anterior, dorsoanterior and dorsal view (Figs. L–N).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1730,1888]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">
