<subSubSection box="[199,1436,369,394]" pageId="3" pageNumber="250" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,538]" box="[199,1436,369,394]" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,369,394]" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[579,750,369,393]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Fistulatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrispinosus">
<emphasis box="[579,750,369,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">quadrispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is derived from this species having four aedeagal processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="250" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,405,430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[589,707,405,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Fistulatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteolus">
<emphasis box="[589,707,405,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">F. luteolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the characters of the pygofer, but can be differentiated from the latter by the aedeagus having a pair of narrow processe in the middle. Also the species is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Fistulatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidentatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">F. bidentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the latter lacks ventral processes of the pygofer and the shape of the aedeagal processes is also different.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
